OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782145126
OL,3,CExtreme heat warnings issued as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to exceed 35C during
OL,5,Cheatwave
OL,7,FIt's already become dangerously hot
OL,8,Facross Europe in the last few days
OL,9,Fwith temperatures exceeding 40C and
OL,10,Fclose to 45C across Spain, Portugal
OL,11,Fand France with many heat warnings in
OL,12,Fplace.
OL,14,FFrance has already seen record
OL,15,Fbreaking temperatures and it's
OL,16,Fpredicted we will see some long
OL,17,Fstanding temperatures smashed in the
OL,18,Fcoming days - both by day and by night.
OL,20,FHow hot is it expected to get?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782145126
OL,3,CExtreme heat warnings issued as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to exceed 35C during
OL,5,Cheatwave
OL,7,FWith temperatures close to 33C on
OL,8,FMonday the hot and humid air will
OL,9,Fbring very warm and restless nights.
OL,10,FThe muggy conditions will add an
OL,11,Funcomfortable feel and make it feel
OL,12,Feven hotter.
OL,14,FThe influence of dangerously hot air
OL,15,Fin France will allow our temperatures
OL,16,Fto climb further into Tuesday and
OL,17,FWednesday, with 36-38C expected and a
OL,18,Fchance of higher figures in places -
OL,19,Fand nights not falling much below
OL,20,Fstuffy and very warm 25C.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782145126
OL,3,CExtreme heat warnings issued as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to exceed 35C during
OL,5,Cheatwave
OL,7,FThe record for nighttime heat stands
OL,8,Fat 22.7C, taken in 1976 and there's a
OL,9,Fhigh chance it will be broken this
OL,10,Fweek.
OL,12,FWe know the summer of 1976 was a
OL,13,Fhistorically hot summer, and the
OL,14,Frecord for hottest June day 35.6C is
OL,15,Flikely to be smashed for the first
OL,16,Ftime in 50 years.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782145126
OL,3,CExtreme heat warnings issued as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to exceed 35C during
OL,5,Cheatwave
OL,7,FWe have seen very hot June days in
OL,8,Frecent years, 34C in 2017 and 2019.
OL,9,FThis time, we are very likely to see
OL,10,Fthis long-standing historical record
OL,11,Fexceeded.
OL,13,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,14,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,15,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,16,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,18,FWhen and where will we see the heat
OL,19,Fpeak?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782145126
OL,3,CExtreme heat warnings issued as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to exceed 35C during
OL,5,Cheatwave
OL,7,FSouthern and South-eastern England
OL,8,Fwill have rocketing temperatures as
OL,9,Fthe week gets underway, with most of
OL,10,FEngland and Wales seeing close to 28-
OL,11,F30C on Monday and 33C.
OL,13,FBy Tuesday, much of England and Wales
OL,14,Fwill be exceeding 30C as it becomes
OL,15,Feven hotter with warm nights and very
OL,16,Fmuggy and humid air.
OL,18,FBy then, we'll see the temperature
OL,19,Freaching close to 36-38C or more in
OL,20,Fsouthern locations - and this extreme
OL,21,Fheat is likely to last a few days.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782145126
OL,3,CExtreme heat warnings issued as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to exceed 35C during
OL,5,Cheatwave
OL,7,FThunderstorms are likely in places,
OL,8,Fwith more clouds helping to cap the
OL,9,Ftemperatures but the heat and humidity
OL,10,Fwill keep it very warm, almost
OL,11,Ftropical-like, both by day and night.
OL,13,FParts of eastern Scotland will heat up
OL,14,Fby midweek, while western Scotland and
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland will always feel more
OL,16,Fcomfortable with more manageable
OL,17,Ftemperatures.
OL,19,FHow long will this intense heatwave
OL,20,Flast?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782145126
OL,3,CExtreme heat warnings issued as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to exceed 35C during
OL,5,Cheatwave
OL,7,FCurrently there's an Amber heat health
OL,8,Falert in place through large parts of
OL,9,Fsouthern England, the Midlands and
OL,10,FWales - this may well be escalated to
OL,11,Fred, the most severe and serious
OL,12,Fwarning.
OL,14,FThe exceptionally hot and humid air is
OL,15,Flooking to be with us most of the week
OL,16,F- and it will take a while for
OL,17,Ftemperatures to slowly lower.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
